  <datafield tag="520" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">We give an elementary proof that Abelian Chern–Simons theory, described as a functor from oriented surfaces to <math altimg="si1.gif" display="inline" id="mml1" overflow="scroll"><msup><mrow><mi>C</mi></mrow><mrow><mo>∗</mo></mrow></msup></math> -algebras, does not admit a natural state. Non-existence of natural states is thus not only a phenomenon of quantum field theories on Lorentzian manifolds, but also of topological quantum field theories formulated in the algebraic approach.</subfield>
